      "source": [
        "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForCausalLM\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load model and tokenizer\n",
        "model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n",
        "\"microsoft/Phi-3-mini-4k-instruct\",\n",
        "device_map=\"cuda\",\n",
        "torch_dtype=\"auto\",\n",
        "trust_remote_code=True,\n",
        ")\n",
        "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"microsoft/Phi-3-mini-4k-instruct\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "83bd0cb2",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "83bd0cb2"
      },
      "source": [
        "we can use the pipeline to combine model, tokenizer and text generation into a single function"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 3,
      "id": "1c97071e",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "1c97071e"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from transformers import pipeline\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create a pipeline\n",
        "generator = pipeline(\n",
        "\"text-generation\",\n",
        "model=model,\n",
        "tokenizer=tokenizer,\n",
        "return_full_text=False,\n",
        "max_new_tokens=500,\n",
        "do_sample=False\n",
        ")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "3ee7d9e2",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3ee7d9e2"
      },
      "source": [
        "return_full_text = false, this ensures only the output of the model returns without prompt\n",
        "\n",
        "max_new tokens, the maximum no of tokens a model can generate, this way we can ensure the model dont produce long heavy outputs, as some models will coontinue generating output until it reaches its context window\n",
        "\n",
        "do_sample, this tells whether the model will use any sampling strategy or not to select the next token, if we set it to false the model will always select the most probable token\n",
        "\n",
        "to generate first text we will tell the model to joke about chicken, to do this we will prompt it using a list of dictionaries where each dic will  relate to an entity in conversation,"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 5,
      "id": "cf53111a",
      "metadata": {
